Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees. Peel the @cassava{1} and remove the pointy ends. Cut the cassava into circles ½cm thick. Pop them on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a splash of @oil{}. Season with a generous pinch of @salt{} and toss well. Roast in your oven for ~{25%minutes}, turn after ~{12%minutes} to make sure they cook evenly.

Next prepare your salsa. Chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into small chunks (ideally ½cm). Pop in a #bowl{} and season with a pinch of @salt{} and mix well. Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and then chop half into small chunks (ideally ½cm or as small as you can). Add these to your tomato. Slice the other half into thin half moon shapes.

Remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and then slice as thinly as you can. Take a quarter of these slices and chop into small cubes. Add this to your red onion and tomato mix. Your salsa is beginning to take shape!

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%sprigs}, zest the @lime{1} and add both to your salsa. Squeeze the lime juice in as well and then stir in the specified quantity of @olive oil{} (see ingredient list). Cut the @red chilli{1} in half lengthways, remove the seeds and then thinly slice. If you want some heat in your salsa add a pinch to start with and keep adding until you have the required level of heat.

Finally, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}. Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat and add a splash of @oil{}. When the oil is hot, add your red onion and pepper and cook for ~{5%minutes} or until soft. Lower the heat to medium and then add your garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} more and then remove from the pan and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{}. Wipe the pan out with #kitchen paper{} and then prepare to cook the sea bream.

When your cassava chips are ready, lower the heat of your oven to 100 degrees and place your stir-fried veggies in your oven to keep warm. Heat the (now empty) frying pan on high heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Pat the @sea bream fillets{2} dry with kitchen paper and season each fillet with a pinch of @salt{} on both sides. Add your bream to the pan skin-side down and leave to cook for ~{3%minutes}.

> The edges of the fish will begin to brown to let you know that the skin is beginning to crisp up!

After 3 mins, carefully turn your bream over and cook for another ~{2-3%minutes}, until the centre of the flesh is white.

Once your bream is cooked get ready to plate up! Arrange a neat pile of your cassava chips on one side of each #plate{}, pop some of your veggies alongside and then place your fish on top. Cover in your salsa, making sure to drizzle over the zesty juices. Serve immediately and enjoy!!